# Portkey Project Conventions

## Stack
- Next.js 15 App Router + TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS custom properties as design tokens)
- Supabase (Postgres + Realtime + Auth)
- TanStack Query for server state
- shadcn/ui components (in src/components/ui/)
- Zod + react-hook-form for forms
- Google Gemini API for AI search

## Naming
- Files: kebab-case (use-trip.ts, trip-card.tsx)
- Components: PascalCase
- Hooks: camelCase prefixed with use-
- API routes: Next.js App Router route handlers (route.ts)

## Import alias
Always use @/* for src/* imports.

## Server vs Client
- Default to Server Components. Add 'use client' only when needed.
- Server Actions in app/actions/ files or inline in Server Components.
- Two Supabase clients: @/lib/supabase/client (browser) and @/lib/supabase/server (server).

## State management
- TanStack Query for all server state (trips, hotels, flights, places).
- React useState/useContext for UI-only state.
- No Redux, no Zustand.

## Forms
- Always react-hook-form + zod resolver. Never uncontrolled forms.

## Error handling
- Use Next.js error.tsx and not-found.tsx boundaries.
- Validate API inputs with Zod. Return typed error responses.
